  "local_port": 48806,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What are the best hotels to stay at in San Francisco?",
  "response": "San Francisco offers a wide range of exceptional hotels, catering to different tastes, budgets, and preferences. Here are some of the best hotels to consider for your stay in the city:\n\n### **Luxury Hotels**\n1. **The Ritz-Carlton, San Francisco**  \n   - Location: Nob Hill  \n   - Features: Classic luxury, plush rooms, fine dining, and a spa.  \n   - Highlights: Known for its impeccable service and elegant ambiance.\n\n2. **Four Seasons Hotel San Francisco**  \n   - Location: SoMa (South of Market)  \n   - Features: Modern luxury, stunning city views, and a rooftop pool.  \n   - Highlights: Great for business and leisure travelers alike.\n\n3. **Fairmont San Francisco**  \n   - Location: Nob Hill  \n   - Features: Historic charm, iconic architecture, and the famous Tonga Room & Hurricane Bar.  \n   - Highlights: Offers panoramic views of the city and bay.\n\n4. **The St. Regis San Francisco**  \n   - Location: SoMa  \n   - Features: Contemporary design, art collection, and a renowned spa.  \n   - Highlights: Excellent service and proximity to cultural attractions.\n\n5. **The Mandarin Oriental, San Francisco**  \n   - Location: Financial District  \n   - Features: Luxurious rooms with bay views, spa, and fine dining.  \n   - Highlights: Perfect for those seeking a high-end, tranquil retreat.\n\n### **Boutique Hotels**\n1. **Hotel Drisco**  \n   - Location: Pacific Heights  \n   - Features: Elegant European-style decor, complimentary breakfast, and evening wine reception.  \n   - Highlights: A quieter, residential setting with personalized service.\n\n2. **The Proper Hotel**  \n   - Location: Mid-Market  \n   - Features: Trendy design, rooftop lounge, and locally inspired cuisine.  \n   - Highlights: Art and culture-focused, with a vibrant atmosphere.\n\n3. **White Swan Inn**  \n   - Location: Nob Hill  \n   - Features: English country-style decor, complimentary breakfast, and afternoon tea.  \n   - Highlights: Romantic and cozy vibe.\n\n4. **The Parker Guest House**  \n   - Location: Mission District  \n   - Features: Victorian charm, garden patio, and complimentary happy hour.  \n   - Highlights: A more intimate and affordable boutique option.\n\n### **Mid-Range Hotels**\n1. **Hotel Zelos**  \n   - Location: SoMa  \n   - Features: Chic design, hip vibe, and a popular restaurant.  \n   - Highlights: Great for younger travelers and those seeking a vibrant scene.\n\n2. **Hotel Vitale**  \n   - Location: Embarcadero  \n   - Features: Bay views, rooftop spa, and eco-friendly practices.  \n   - Highlights: Close to the waterfront and Ferry Building.\n\n3. **Kimpton Alton Hotel**  \n   - Location: Fisherman\u2019s Wharf  \n   - Features: Bright, modern rooms, pet-friendly, and complimentary wine hour.  \n   - Highlights: Convenient for exploring tourist attractions.\n\n### **Budget-Friendly Options**\n1. **The Phoenix Hotel**  \n   - Location: Tenderloin  \n   - Features: Retro vibe, pool, and live music events.  \n   - Highlights: A favorite for creatives and music lovers.\n\n2. **Hotel G**  \n   - Location: Union Square  \n   - Features: Compact, stylish rooms and a central location.  \n   - Highlights: Affordable and hip, with great access to shopping and dining.\n\n3. **The Mosser Hotel**  \n   - Location: SoMa  \n   - Features: Industrial design, budget-friendly, and eco-conscious.  \n   - Highlights: Great value for a central location.\n\n### **Unique Stays**\n1. **The Line SF**  \n   - Location: Tenderloin  \n   - Features: Artsy vibe, local art installations, and a popular bar and restaurant.  \n   - Highlights: A modern, community-focused hotel.\n\n2. **Inn at the Presidio**  \n   - Location: Presidio  \n   - Features: Historic setting, complimentary breakfast, and evening wine and cheese reception.  \n   - Highlights: Surrounded by nature and hiking trails.\n\n3. **Hotel Boh\u00e8me**  \n   - Location: North Beach  \n   - Features: Bohemian d\u00e9cor, literary and Beatnik history.  \n   - Highlights: Perfect for those wanting to explore the artsy North Beach neighborhood.\n\nWhen choosing a hotel, consider your priorities, such as location, budget, and amenities, as San Francisco has something for everyone!",
  "temperature": 1.0,
